      • point

        @NonNull
static Point point(double x,
                            double y)
        Creates a point from the given coordinates.

        This is just a shortcut to Point.fromCoordinates(double, double). It is duplicated here so that Geo can be used as a single entry point in Gremlin-groovy scripts.

      • lineString

        @NonNull
static LineString lineString(@NonNull
                                      Point point1,
                                      @NonNull
                                      Point point2,
                                      @NonNull
                                      Point... otherPoints)
        Creates a line string from the given (at least 2) points.

        This is just a shortcut to LineString.fromPoints(Point, Point, Point...). It is duplicated here so that Geo can be used as a single entry point in Gremlin-groovy scripts.

      • lineString

        @NonNull
static LineString lineString(double... coordinates)
        Creates a line string from the coordinates of its points.

        This is provided for backward compatibility with previous DSE versions. We recommend lineString(Point, Point, Point...) instead.

      • polygon

                                Point p1,

                                Point p2,

                                Point p3,

                                Point... otherPoints)
        Creates a polygon from the given (at least 3) points.

        This is just a shortcut to Polygon.fromPoints(Point, Point, Point, Point...). It is duplicated here so that Geo can be used as a single entry point in Gremlin-groovy scripts.

      • polygon

        @NonNull
static Polygon polygon(double... coordinates)
